<html>
	<head>
		<title>BCM_GETTEXT</title>
		<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
	</head>
	<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
		<p><font color="#000000" size="4"><strong>BCM_LOADPARSER</strong></font></p>
		<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="3" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td width="100%" bgcolor="#e6e6e6"><pre>BCM_LOADPARSER
	wParam = ( WPARAM )( BOOL )bFromMemory;
	lParam = ( LPARAM )( LPCTSTR )lpszFilename;
	lParam = ( LPARAM )( HGLOBAL )hMemHandle;</pre>
				</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
		<p>Load a parser file from a file or a memory handle. Returns non-zero for success or 
			zero for failure.</p>
		<DL>
			<DT><EM>bFromMemory<BR>
				</EM>
				<dd>
					This must be set to TRUE if the parser file is to be loaded from a global 
					memory handle and FALSE if the parser is to be loaded from a file. <dt><em>lpszFilename<BR>
							hMemHandle</em>
						<dd>
							This is either&nbsp;the global memory handle (WPARAM = TRUE)&nbsp;or a pointer 
							to&nbsp;a 0-terminated&nbsp;string containing the full path of the parser file 
							(WPARAM = FALSE).&nbsp;&nbsp;</dd></DL>
		<P><STRONG>NOTES</STRONG>:
			<BR>
			The loaded parser will be valid for&nbsp;<STRONG>all</STRONG> Brainchild 
			controls which have been created by the calling thread. Requires at least 
			version 2.2 of brainchild.
		</P>
	</body>
</html>
